Traffic has also been disrupted on Govan Mbeki Road between Duinefontein Road and Emms Drive. CAPE TOWN - The Gugulethu fire station has been set alight by protesters. It will remain closed on Thursday. Traffic has also been disrupted on Govan Mbeki Road between Duinefontein Road and Emms Drive. SAPS and Metro Police officials are on scene. Fire and Rescue's Theo Layne: "Firefighters were forced to vacate the premises and remained in the drill yard until Metro Police and law enforcement dispersed the protesters. The front of the station sustained severe damage, including the watch room engine bay doors (sic)." 